P(C) = \sum_{i=0}^x i \bigcup A 
P(C) = \sum_{i=0}^x (P(i) + P(A) - P(i)*P(A))
P(C) = \sum_{i=0}^x (P(i) + P(A)) - \sum_{i=0}^x (P(i) * P(A))
P(C) = P(A)x - P(A)^x
\frac{P(C)}{P(A)} = x - P(A)^{x-1} 
Log(\frac{P(C)}{P(A)} - x ) = Log(P(A)^{x-1})
Log(\frac{P(C)}{P(A)} - x ) = (x-1)Log(P(A))
